# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: MagePath | Scene: MagePath11
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah and Xan arrived back at the throne room."
    new "Sarah and Xan arrived back at the throne room."

    old "When they had left, it was empty, but by now the first army units of the Mythran army had begun to swarm in."
    new "When they had left, it was empty, but by now the first army units of the Mythran army had begun to swarm in."

    old "It was nothing like before, when Sarah had faced a small advance group of poorly armed mercenaries."
    new "It was nothing like before, when Sarah had faced a small advance group of poorly armed mercenaries."

    old "This was a real army."
    new "This was a real army."

    old "Hundreds of men, marching in formation, bearing full plate armor. Swords, lances, bows."
    new "Hundreds of men, marching in formation, bearing full plate armor. Swords, lances, bows."

    old "They were ready for everything."
    new "They were ready for everything."

    old "One man marched at the front of the soldiers. His armor was covered in intricate designs, seperating him from the ordinary soldiers."
    new "One man marched at the front of the soldiers. His armor was covered in intricate designs, seperating him from the ordinary soldiers."

    old "The least you can do is die with some honour."
    new "The least you can do is die with some honour."

    old "Following after him, was his daughter Samayra."
    new "Following after him, was his daughter Samayra."

    old "Seeing the moment, and how fast things could turn, Sarah nudged Xan, urging him to take action."
    new "Seeing the moment, and how fast things could turn, Sarah nudged Xan, urging him to take action."

    old "Xan stepped forward, in between the two warring factions."
    new "Xan stepped forward, in between the two warring factions."

    old "Greetings, great prince of Mythran. My name is Xanthippe. I am here on behalf of my order, and I have vowed to safeguard the Bagrad royal family."
    new "Greetings, great prince of Mythran. My name is Xanthippe. I am here on behalf of my order, and I have vowed to safeguard the Bagrad royal family."

    old "I would wish to speak with you about a peaceful surrender, one that acknowledges your great victory here, but one that also sees that the royal family will come to no harm."
    new "I would wish to speak with you about a peaceful surrender, one that acknowledges your great victory here, but one that also sees that the royal family will come to no harm."

    old "The reputation of your people tells me you are a civilized folk, one that has no love for brutality, so I urge you, allow the royal family dignity in their defeat."
    new "The reputation of your people tells me you are a civilized folk, one that has no love for brutality, so I urge you, allow the royal family dignity in their defeat."

    old "The Mythran prince raised one eyebrow."
    new "The Mythran prince raised one eyebrow."

    old "What trouble is any of this to your order?"
    new "What trouble is any of this to your order?"

    old "The royal family of Bagrad has been true friends to our order for centuries, and so we wish to facilitate a graceful surrender."
    new "The royal family of Bagrad has been true friends to our order for centuries, and so we wish to facilitate a graceful surrender."

    old "The Mythran prince laughed, his voice echoing through the vast throne room."
    new "The Mythran prince laughed, his voice echoing through the vast throne room."

    old "Where was this concern for protocol and politeness when that decrepit creature stabbed my nephew to death?"
    new "Where was this concern for protocol and politeness when that decrepit creature stabbed my nephew to death?"

    old "Over what was it, again Shah? A rude comment?"
    new "Over what was it, again Shah? A rude comment?"

    old "The Mythran Prince shook his head."
    new "The Mythran Prince shook his head."

    old "No, I think I'll do whatever I want to them, as is my right by conquest. And your order can go back to ignoring whatever else happens in the world."
    new "No, I think I'll do whatever I want to them, as is my right by conquest. And your order can go back to ignoring whatever else happens in the world."

    old "He'll die slowly and violently. As for his daughter, she'll make for a fine reward for my men and I'll sell her off on some slave market after."
    new "He'll die slowly and violently. As for his daughter, she'll make for a fine reward for my men and I'll sell her off on some slave market after."

    old "I warn you, if you try to do so, you leave me no choice but to intercede."
    new "I warn you, if you try to do so, you leave me no choice but to intercede."

    old "Again, the Mythran prince could only laugh."
    new "Again, the Mythran prince could only laugh."

    old "Really? I'd advise you to think about that again."
    new "Really? I'd advise you to think about that again."

    old "Right now, you and your associate there are simply mages, and by Mythran policy, we take a position of neutrality on your order."
    new "Right now, you and your associate there are simply mages, and by Mythran policy, we take a position of neutrality on your order."

    old "That means you're free to leave. Even if I suspect you probably killed more than a few of my men."
    new "That means you're free to leave. Even if I suspect you probably killed more than a few of my men."

    old "But my soldiers here are well trained, seasoned and armed to the teeth. There are even some anti-magic weapons among their ranks."
    new "But my soldiers here are well trained, seasoned and armed to the teeth. There are even some anti-magic weapons among their ranks."

    old "You wouldn't be the first mage we killed either..."
    new "You wouldn't be the first mage we killed either..."

    old "The prince stared directly at Xan."
    new "The prince stared directly at Xan."

    old "So, raise your hand, and I'll just as easily kill you and your apprentice."
    new "So, raise your hand, and I'll just as easily kill you and your apprentice."

    old "Or...simply walk away, and you have my word, nobody will so much as lay a hand on you."
    new "Or...simply walk away, and you have my word, nobody will so much as lay a hand on you."

    old "Xan turned to Sarah and spoke in whispers."
    new "Xan turned to Sarah and spoke in whispers."

    old "We need to leave, while we still can..."
    new "We need to leave, while we still can..."

    old "Xan...you can't do that...we promised them..."
    new "Xan...you can't do that...we promised them..."

    old "And they'll be dead soon. What does it matter if we keep a promise to a dead man?"
    new "And they'll be dead soon. What does it matter if we keep a promise to a dead man?"

    old "They don't deserve this...she doesn't deserve this..."
    new "They don't deserve this...she doesn't deserve this..."

    old "So what do you want me to do? He's right, if we fight them, we'll die. What good will that do?"
    new "So what do you want me to do? He's right, if we fight them, we'll die. What good will that do?"

    old "Admit it. We lost, it happens sometimes. We stil have what we came here for, as for the royal family...whatever happens, happens."
    new "Admit it. We lost, it happens sometimes. We stil have what we came here for, as for the royal family...whatever happens, happens."

    old "Xan began to walk away, but Sarah found herself unable to move."
    new "Xan began to walk away, but Sarah found herself unable to move."

    old "Her eyes found those of Samayra."
    new "Her eyes found those of Samayra."

    old "She could spot the fear in the Bagrad princess, her eyes begging her to stay."
    new "She could spot the fear in the Bagrad princess, her eyes begging her to stay."

    old "Sarah couldn't bring herself to follow Xan, even as she watched him walk away."
    new "Sarah couldn't bring herself to follow Xan, even as she watched him walk away."

    old "Xan turned around and spoke louder."
    new "Xan turned around and spoke louder."

    old "Sarah! Come, immediately."
    new "Sarah! Come, immediately."

    old "And still, she couldn't."
    new "And still, she couldn't."

    old "As I suspected."
    new "As I suspected."

    old "The Shah's imperious voice cut through the room, all attention centering on him."
    new "The Shah's imperious voice cut through the room, all attention centering on him."

    old "Aah! It speaks, finally."
    new "Aah! It speaks, finally."

    old "The Mythran prince laughed as he spoke, mocking the Shah."
    new "The Mythran prince laughed as he spoke, mocking the Shah."

    old "You offered your word to me mage, and now we see what it is worth. Now everyone can see."
    new "You offered your word to me mage, and now we see what it is worth. Now everyone can see."

    old "We did all we could for you, Shah Mahda, but these events are now out of our control."
    new "We did all we could for you, Shah Mahda, but these events are now out of our control."

    old "You have our sympathies."
    new "You have our sympathies."

    old "Your sympathies..."
    new "Your sympathies..."

    old "That seems to be about all I ever purchased from you, despite everything."
    new "That seems to be about all I ever purchased from you, despite everything."

    old "Xan turned back to Sarah again."
    new "Xan turned back to Sarah again."

    old "Sarah, we need to leave, now!"
    new "Sarah, we need to leave, now!"

    old "Sarah watched the scene before her. To abandon the royal family felt like a betrayal she could not endure."
    new "Sarah watched the scene before her. To abandon the royal family felt like a betrayal she could not endure."

    old "And yet, neither could she fight this army."
    new "And yet, neither could she fight this army."

    old "She could neither fight nor leave. Each option seemed impossible to her, and so instead, she was trapped in inaction."
    new "She could neither fight nor leave. Each option seemed impossible to her, and so instead, she was trapped in inaction."

    old "But in that place, something occured to her."
    new "But in that place, something occured to her."

    old "There was something odd about the scene."
    new "There was something odd about the scene."

    old "The Shah, prone to rage, appeared calmer than she had ever seen him."
    new "The Shah, prone to rage, appeared calmer than she had ever seen him."

    old "Was this how a man carried himself when he faced torture and horror to himself and his family?"
    new "Was this how a man carried himself when he faced torture and horror to himself and his family?"

    old "Something was wrong."
    new "Something was wrong."

    old "I suppose it was my mistake, believing that I could ally myself with a mage."
    new "I suppose it was my mistake, believing that I could ally myself with a mage."

    old "Sarah! Let's go!"
    new "Sarah! Let's go!"

    old "Xan was all but screaming by now."
    new "Xan was all but screaming by now."

    old "But you see, my dynasty hails back centuries, and we have more allies than your decrepit order."
    new "But you see, my dynasty hails back centuries, and we have more allies than your decrepit order."

    old "Enough of this blabber, soldiers! Seize him!"
    new "Enough of this blabber, soldiers! Seize him!"

    old "Sarah watched as the Shah removed an object from his pockets."
    new "Sarah watched as the Shah removed an object from his pockets."

    old "A dagger."
    new "A dagger."

    old "But this was no ordinary dagger, rather, its blade shined with a deep crimson red light. A colour she had only ever seen once before in her life, earlier that day."
    new "But this was no ordinary dagger, rather, its blade shined with a deep crimson red light. A colour she had only ever seen once before in her life, earlier that day."

    old "She could see Xan's face warp into one of utter terror."
    new "She could see Xan's face warp into one of utter terror."

    old "With a single, decisive slash, the Shah swiped the dagger across the air."
    new "With a single, decisive slash, the Shah swiped the dagger across the air."

    old "But it did not cut the air, rather, it cut deeper still."
    new "But it did not cut the air, rather, it cut deeper still."

    old "Trailing the path of the dagger was a wound, one that injured the world itself. Sarah nearly cried out at it, so fundamentally abhorrent did it appear to her."
    new "Trailing the path of the dagger was a wound, one that injured the world itself. Sarah nearly cried out at it, so fundamentally abhorrent did it appear to her."

    old "The rend that drew across the world began to grow and expand, tearing itself apart."
    new "The rend that drew across the world began to grow and expand, tearing itself apart."

    old "From within or beyond, something drew near."
    new "From within or beyond, something drew near."

    old "Two sets of claws rose out, seizing the edges of the mutilated space, and ripped apart. What was once a slash across reality, was now a festering open sore."
    new "Two sets of claws rose out, seizing the edges of the mutilated space, and ripped apart. What was once a slash across reality, was now a festering open sore."

    old "Rising out from the impossibility, an impossible creature."
    new "Rising out from the impossibility, an impossible creature."

    old "Black as a night without moonlight, its only definable features were a set of razor sharp teeth, emerging from what had to pass for a head, and a pale mask that sat upon where its face should have been."
    new "Black as a night without moonlight, its only definable features were a set of razor sharp teeth, emerging from what had to pass for a head, and a pale mask that sat upon where its face should have been."

    old "The thing slithered out from its world, ready to be born into this one."
    new "The thing slithered out from its world, ready to be born into this one."

    old "In dread silence, all had witnessed the birth of this unholy creation, but now, the thing was real. And the fear followed."
    new "In dread silence, all had witnessed the birth of this unholy creation, but now, the thing was real. And the fear followed."

    old "Soldiers began to scream, the Mythran prince only stood stunned, unable to respond."
    new "Soldiers began to scream, the Mythran prince only stood stunned, unable to respond."

    old "Sarah felt Xan's hand grip her wrist."
    new "Sarah felt Xan's hand grip her wrist."

    old "We leave, now!"
    new "We leave, now!"

    old "She was too stunned to resist and felt herself being dragged along."
    new "She was too stunned to resist and felt herself being dragged along."

    old "The beast began its attack."
    new "The beast began its attack."

    old "Lunging forward like a snake, the creature snapped its titanic jaw around the head of the Mythran prince, snapping it clean off."
    new "Lunging forward like a snake, the creature snapped its titanic jaw around the head of the Mythran prince, snapping it clean off."

    old "A black, oily tongue, emerged from its mouth, sliding around the body of the Mythran prince, and dragging it into its bowels."
    new "A black, oily tongue, emerged from its mouth, sliding around the body of the Mythran prince, and dragging it into its bowels."

    old "Were it not for Xan pulling her, Sarah realized she would never have found the courage to move."
    new "Were it not for Xan pulling her, Sarah realized she would never have found the courage to move."

    old "The soldiers, trained and battle-hardened, took up their arms and surrounded the creature, as if it were a thing that could be fought."
    new "The soldiers, trained and battle-hardened, took up their arms and surrounded the creature, as if it were a thing that could be fought."

    old "With lightning speed, the creature spun and turned, wipping its tail across the front line."
    new "With lightning speed, the creature spun and turned, wipping its tail across the front line."

    old "A red mist splattered out as the sheer force of the creature's tail ripped them apart."
    new "A red mist splattered out as the sheer force of the creature's tail ripped them apart."

    old "When the soldiers saw how the bravest among them had been slaughtered with ease, fear took hold of them too."
    new "When the soldiers saw how the bravest among them had been slaughtered with ease, fear took hold of them too."

    old "Dropping their weapons, many began to run."
    new "Dropping their weapons, many began to run."

    old "But the beast tolerated no defiance nor cowardice."
    new "But the beast tolerated no defiance nor cowardice."

    old "Launching itself by the strength of its tail, it rushed forward, ripping through countless soldiers as it positioned itself near the door, barring any escape."
    new "Launching itself by the strength of its tail, it rushed forward, ripping through countless soldiers as it positioned itself near the door, barring any escape."

    old "Again, it snapped forward, catching another soldier with its teeth and slowly consuming it."
    new "Again, it snapped forward, catching another soldier with its teeth and slowly consuming it."

    old "By now, everyone in the room had surrendered to a frenzied madness. The kind that only came over those who knew death would soon take them."
    new "By now, everyone in the room had surrendered to a frenzied madness. The kind that only came over those who knew death would soon take them."

    old "Soldiers tried to escape into different directions, but the room offered no escape. One by one, the vile creature tore them apart."
    new "Soldiers tried to escape into different directions, but the room offered no escape. One by one, the vile creature tore them apart."

    old "The army, once a shining examplar of military discipline, had entirely collapsed."
    new "The army, once a shining examplar of military discipline, had entirely collapsed."

    old "Booming out over the slaughter was the Shah's laugh, a mad cackle."
    new "Booming out over the slaughter was the Shah's laugh, a mad cackle."

    old "A man who knew he had killed himself just the same, but took glee from knowing his enemies would die with him."
    new "A man who knew he had killed himself just the same, but took glee from knowing his enemies would die with him."

    old "Xan and Sarah reached the end of the room."
    new "Xan and Sarah reached the end of the room."

    old "Xan placed his hand on the wall, and with a concentrated blast of magic, ripped a hole through it."
    new "Xan placed his hand on the wall, and with a concentrated blast of magic, ripped a hole through it."

    old "Ok, this will get us out, we need to get to the warp point that takes us back to the house, alright?"
    new "Ok, this will get us out, we need to get to the warp point that takes us back to the house, alright?"

    old "Sarah was dazed."
    new "Sarah was dazed."

    old "Listen to me Sarah, we need to keep moving, we can't afford a single mistake right now."
    new "Listen to me Sarah, we need to keep moving, we can't afford a single mistake right now."

    old "Back to the house, alright?"
    new "Back to the house, alright?"

    old "This seemed to bring Sarah back to herself."
    new "This seemed to bring Sarah back to herself."

    old "Then, an ear shattering scream rang out over the room."
    new "Then, an ear shattering scream rang out over the room."

    old "There, on the far side of the throne room, cowering behind the throne, Sarah could see Samayra."
    new "There, on the far side of the throne room, cowering behind the throne, Sarah could see Samayra."

    old "Among the chaos, everyone, even her father, had forgotten about her."
    new "Among the chaos, everyone, even her father, had forgotten about her."

    old "Save Samayra."
    new "Save Samayra."

    old "Sarah knew she could never leave Samayra to die."
    new "Sarah knew she could never leave Samayra to die."

    old "I have to save her."
    new "I have to save her."

    old "Sarah begins to sprint back through the throne room."
    new "Sarah begins to sprint back through the throne room."

    old "Sarah, get back!"
    new "Sarah, get back!"

    old "But she's already too far gone for the mage to stop her."
    new "But she's already too far gone for the mage to stop her."

    old "With every step, faster and faster, she feels her heels stomping hard into the stone floor."
    new "With every step, faster and faster, she feels her heels stomping hard into the stone floor."

    old "The sound of her running is drowned out by the sound of the slaughter as the beast makes it's way, carving through what remains of the soldiers."
    new "The sound of her running is drowned out by the sound of the slaughter as the beast makes it's way, carving through what remains of the soldiers."

    old "She feels her lungs beginning to burn as she pushes herself on."
    new "She feels her lungs beginning to burn as she pushes herself on."

    old "Samayra!"
    new "Samayra!"

    old "Sarah calls out to the princess. She begs that she will notice her."
    new "Sarah calls out to the princess. She begs that she will notice her."

    old "Samayra!!!"
    new "Samayra!!!"

    old "The second time, the girl looks up to her. For but a moment, fear fades from her face."
    new "The second time, the girl looks up to her. For but a moment, fear fades from her face."

    old "Sarah! Help me, please!"
    new "Sarah! Help me, please!"

    old "Sarah runs up the steps to the throne, so long are her steps that she all but climbs up to the throne in less than three leaps."
    new "Sarah runs up the steps to the throne, so long are her steps that she all but climbs up to the throne in less than three leaps."

    old "Grab my hand!"
    new "Grab my hand!"

    old "Samayra reaches out and holds onto Sarah."
    new "Samayra reaches out and holds onto Sarah."

    old "Whatever you do, don't let go. We have to keep moving."
    new "Whatever you do, don't let go. We have to keep moving."

    old "Off in the distance, Sarah hears the sound of breaking metal and shattering bones, as the beast continues to feed."
    new "Off in the distance, Sarah hears the sound of breaking metal and shattering bones, as the beast continues to feed."

    old "She cannot see the Shah anymore, nor hear his laughter. Did he die? She can't be sure. She also can't afford to waste time."
    new "She cannot see the Shah anymore, nor hear his laughter. Did he die? She can't be sure. She also can't afford to waste time."

    old "Together, the two begin to run."
    new "Together, the two begin to run."

    old "Each prays the creature will not notice them. Prays that it will release its rage on someone else."
    new "Each prays the creature will not notice them. Prays that it will release its rage on someone else."

    old "They cross the vast throne room, each near exhaustion as they finally get back to the exit that Xan had made."
    new "They cross the vast throne room, each near exhaustion as they finally get back to the exit that Xan had made."

    old "They stumble into the hallways of Bagrad palace, for the first time since it began, feeling even a faint sense of safety."
    new "They stumble into the hallways of Bagrad palace, for the first time since it began, feeling even a faint sense of safety."

    old "You risked everything!"
    new "You risked everything!"

    old "Sarah is breathing heavily, so close to exhaustion. She wants to fall to her knees, but she knows they're not safe yet."
    new "Sarah is breathing heavily, so close to exhaustion. She wants to fall to her knees, but she knows they're not safe yet."

    old "How could you be that foolish? For what?"
    new "How could you be that foolish? For what?"

    old "Sarah snaps at Xan, for the first time."
    new "Sarah snaps at Xan, for the first time."

    old "I said I would protect her, and I did. You might break your word, but I keep mine, and I don't need a lecture from you."
    new "I said I would protect her, and I did. You might break your word, but I keep mine, and I don't need a lecture from you."

    old "Xan is quiet for a while, then chooses not to respond."
    new "Xan is quiet for a while, then chooses not to respond."

    old "The waypoint is over by the far end of the hall, just as when we first arrived."
    new "The waypoint is over by the far end of the hall, just as when we first arrived."

    old "Come, we'll be safe soon."
    new "Come, we'll be safe soon."

    old "Samayra doesn't say much, only nodding."
    new "Samayra doesn't say much, only nodding."

    old "Together, all three move down the hall."
    new "Together, all three move down the hall."

    old "There are sounds of battle, and behind them, more screams from the throne room. Other than that, the palace is empty."
    new "There are sounds of battle, and behind them, more screams from the throne room. Other than that, the palace is empty."

    old "No more guards. No more soldiers."
    new "No more guards. No more soldiers."

    old "Past here."
    new "Past here."

    old "Xan leads them through the door, leading through more corridors, and finally, appearing before the waypoint."
    new "Xan leads them through the door, leading through more corridors, and finally, appearing before the waypoint."

    old "The waypoint. The magical portal that connected between Xan's house and the palace. Only when correctly manipulated did it function, otherwise, it was a door like any other."
    new "The waypoint. The magical portal that connected between Xan's house and the palace. Only when correctly manipulated did it function, otherwise, it was a door like any other."

    old "Xan turned to Sarah and Samayra."
    new "Xan turned to Sarah and Samayra."

    old "Fine, you saved the girl, but this is as far as it goes. She'll have to take care of herself."
    new "Fine, you saved the girl, but this is as far as it goes. She'll have to take care of herself."

    old "Sarah could feel a rage build inside of her."
    new "Sarah could feel a rage build inside of her."

    old "No. She's coming with us, back to the house, where she is actually safe."
    new "No. She's coming with us, back to the house, where she is actually safe."

    old "Sarah, we can't go around saving everyone! It's not our place, and it's not what is meant to happen."
    new "Sarah, we can't go around saving everyone! It's not our place, and it's not what is meant to happen."

    old "Sarah sighed, she was far too angry and far too tired to deal with this now."
    new "Sarah sighed, she was far too angry and far too tired to deal with this now."

    old "I don't care about rules or about what is meant to happen."
    new "I don't care about rules or about what is meant to happen."

    old "I'm telling you, she's coming with us, no matter what. I'm not asking."
    new "I'm telling you, she's coming with us, no matter what. I'm not asking."

    old "She stared Xan down, until finally, he relented."
    new "She stared Xan down, until finally, he relented."

    old "We will speak of this later, I promise you that!"
    new "We will speak of this later, I promise you that!"

    old "Xan waved his hand across the handle of the door, and opened it, revealing the entrance to the house."
    new "Xan waved his hand across the handle of the door, and opened it, revealing the entrance to the house."

    old "They stepped through and the door was closed behind them, sealing the exit."
    new "They stepped through and the door was closed behind them, sealing the exit."

    old "And with a single step, they breached a distance of a million steps."
    new "And with a single step, they breached a distance of a million steps."

    old "Back in Lethram, as if they never left."
    new "Back in Lethram, as if they never left."

    old "Sarah watched as Samayra collapsed to the floor, falling onto her hands and knees."
    new "Sarah watched as Samayra collapsed to the floor, falling onto her hands and knees."

    old "She knelt down next to her, placing her hand on her back, trying to ease her breathing."
    new "She knelt down next to her, placing her hand on her back, trying to ease her breathing."

    old "Hey, it's ok, we're safe, don't worry."
    new "Hey, it's ok, we're safe, don't worry."

    old "She kept offering soothing words, hoping to calm her."
    new "She kept offering soothing words, hoping to calm her."

    old "Xan was pacing back and forth."
    new "Xan was pacing back and forth."

    old "What a disaster this turned out to be..."
    new "What a disaster this turned out to be..."

    old "Do you know what that thing was?"
    new "Do you know what that thing was?"

    old "Xan stopped pacing and looked at her."
    new "Xan stopped pacing and looked at her."

    old "It's just like Razaphel, a voidling."
    new "It's just like Razaphel, a voidling."

    old "But...it looked so different."
    new "But...it looked so different."

    old "They come in all kinds of shapes, and I'll admit, this one was bigger than the usual kind."
    new "They come in all kinds of shapes, and I'll admit, this one was bigger than the usual kind."

    old "What happens to it now?"
    new "What happens to it now?"

    old "They can't survive in our world for very long. It will rage for a few days, then slowly collapse and die."
    new "They can't survive in our world for very long. It will rage for a few days, then slowly collapse and die."

    old "The idea of that nightmare existing for days horrified her, but she was still glad to know it wouldn't last."
    new "The idea of that nightmare existing for days horrified her, but she was still glad to know it wouldn't last."

    old "The real question I feel like dealing with is this."
    new "The real question I feel like dealing with is this."

    old "Xan waved his hand in Samayra's direction."
    new "Xan waved his hand in Samayra's direction."

    old "Not now."
    new "Not now."

    old "She's been through a lot, she needs to get her rest. We can discuss this later, when it's just you and me."
